3:["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Vertex calculates funding rates every hour using a time-weighted average price between perpetual and index prices. The exchange uses cross-margin by default, allowing ATOM positions to be margined against other assets in your portfolio. Funding payments occur automatically at the top of each hour, with rates determined by the premium/discount of the perpetual relative to Cosmos's spot price across major exchanges."}]
4:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["Why ","ATOM","/","USDT","?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"ATOM/USDT on Vertex presents unique arbitrage opportunities due to Cosmos ecosystem developments and staking narrative volatility. The pair often exhibits funding rate divergence from centralized exchanges during Cosmos governance events or Inter-Blockchain Communication protocol updates."}]]}]
5:["$","section","0",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Historical Funding Rate Patterns"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"ATOM funding rates on Vertex typically range from -0.01% to +0.05% hourly, with extreme rates reaching ±0.1% during major Cosmos ecosystem announcements. The pair shows pronounced funding spikes during liquid staking developments and validator set changes. Patterns indicate higher positive funding during US trading hours when retail interest in Layer 1 tokens peaks. Correlation analysis shows ATOM funding often moves inversely to Bitcoin dominance periods."}]]}]
6:["$","section","1",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Arbitrage Opportunities"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Vertex's low taker fees (0.02%) create profitable arbitrage windows when funding rates exceed 0.03% hourly. Cross-margin capabilities enable delta-neutral strategies using ATOM spot positions against perpetual shorts. The hybrid DEX structure allows for faster execution than traditional AMMs while maintaining on-chain settlement. Opportunities often arise during Cosmos airdrops when perpetual demand spikes while spot remains stable on centralized venues."}]]}]
7:["$","section","2",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Risk Considerations"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Vertex operates on Arbitrum, introducing smart contract risk and potential sequencer downtime affecting position management. The exchange's lower liquidity compared to major CEXs can lead to wider spreads during volatile periods. Cross-margin positions require careful monitoring as ATOM's correlation with other crypto assets can create unexpected liquidation scenarios. Funding rate arbitrage profits may be offset by basis risk if unable to hedge effectively across venues during extreme market conditions."}]]}]
8:["$","$Ld",null,{"items":[{"question":"How often are ATOM/USDT funding rates updated on Vertex?","answer":"Vertex updates ATOM/USDT funding rates every hour at the top of the hour. The rate is calculated using the previous hour's time-weighted average premium between the perpetual and index price, with payments automatically settled to long or short positions."},{"question":"What makes Vertex different from other DEXs for ATOM perpetuals?","answer":"Vertex uses a hybrid architecture combining on-chain risk management with off-chain sequencer execution, providing faster order matching than traditional AMMs. The platform offers cross-margin by default, allowing ATOM positions to be margined against your entire portfolio rather than isolated margin."},{"question":"Can I hedge ATOM perpetual positions on Vertex with spot holdings?","answer":"Yes, Vertex's cross-margin system allows you to use ATOM spot holdings as collateral for perpetual positions. This enables delta-neutral funding rate strategies where you can short ATOM perpetuals while holding equivalent spot amounts to capture funding payments."},{"question":"What are the main risks of ATOM funding arbitrage on Vertex?","answer":"Key risks include Arbitrum sequencer downtime affecting position management, lower liquidity leading to execution slippage, and cross-margin liquidation risk if other portfolio assets move adversely. Smart contract risk is also present as Vertex is a relatively newer protocol compared to established centralized exchanges."}]}]
